<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 6:30AM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Calhoun, Jackson,
Ingham and southern Eaton Counties through 730 AM EDT...
At 630 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marshall, moving northeast at 70 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Jackson...             Albion...              Mason...
Marshall...            Battle Creek...        Eaton Rapids...
Williamston...         Leslie...              Homer...
Bellevue...            Stockbridge...         Grass Lake...
Brownlee Park...       Vandercook Lake...     Leoni...
Spring Arbor...        Sandstone...           Aurelius...
Onondaga...            Marengo...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
